---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Spirit Mirror">

<div class="about">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-inner">
      <p class="about-eyebrow">Our story</p>
      <h1 class="about-title">We believe understanding<br />starts with <em>listening</em></h1>
      <p class="about-lead">Spirit Mirror exists to help people truly see each other — not through the lens of politics or headlines, but through the quiet, profound things that shape who people are: how they raise their children, what they believe, the stories they tell, the rituals that mark their lives.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <div class="about-text-block">
        <h2 class="about-h2">The problem we are trying to solve</h2>
        <p>Most cultural information is surface-level. You read a Wikipedia article, you learn some dates, you memorize some facts — and you feel like you understand. But you don't. You understand a description of a culture, not the lived experience of it.</p>
        <p>We are living through a period of unprecedented cultural friction. People who have never met each other are making decisions that affect each other's lives — voters, policymakers, neighbors — based on stereotypes, inherited prejudices, and headlines that reward outrage over understanding.</p>
        <p>At the same time, most people genuinely want to understand each other. They just lack the framework to go deeper.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-aside">
        <blockquote class="about-quote">"The single greatest barrier to human connection is the assumption that others experience the world the way we do."</blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framework -->
  <section class="about-section about-section--alt">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <div class="about-text-block">
        <h2 class="about-h2">The framework: pillars of identity</h2>
        <p>We believe the way a person thinks — what makes them who they are, how they see the world — is built from a set of cultural pillars. These are not opinions or choices. They are the deep architecture of a person's identity, absorbed before they are old enough to question it.</p>
        <p>To understand a people, you need to understand their pillars:</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-pillars">
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">🧒</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>Parenting</h3>
            <p>How a culture raises its children shapes every adult that culture produces. The values, habits, and expectations instilled in childhood are the foundation of adult worldview.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">📖</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>Traditional Stories</h3>
            <p>The tales told to children, the myths that explain the world's origins, the folk heroes and tricksters — these encode the moral imagination of a people.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">📜</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>History</h3>
            <p>Not the textbook version — the lived experience. What a people have survived, what they have built, what they have lost. History is not just what happened; it is what a people remember.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">🙏</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>Belief</h3>
            <p>What people believe about the divine, about death, about what happens after — these are the questions that shape every other answer. Belief is the ultimate context.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">🪔</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>Traditional Rituals</h3>
            <p>The ceremonies that mark the milestones of life — birth, coming of age, marriage, death. These are the moments when culture is most visible and most deeply felt.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-pillar">
          <div class="about-pillar-icon">🎆</div>
          <div class="about-pillar-content">
            <h3>Festivals</h3>
            <p>What a people celebrate, and how, reveals what they value. Festivals are集体 memory made festive — the past year's harvest, a historical victory, a divine visitation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-text-block">
        <p>Some cultures have additional pillars that define them particularly strongly — music, literature, dance, cinema, visual art. These are optional enrichments that add texture and depth.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we're not -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <div class="about-text-block">
        <h2 class="about-h2">What we are — and what we are not</h2>
        <p>Spirit Mirror is not a travel guide. You will not find restaurant recommendations or hotel tips here. It is not a Wikipedia article. It does not summarize — it <em>excavates</em>.</p>
        <p>We are not claiming that understanding a culture's pillars will make you an expert on every individual from that culture. People are individuals. They contain multitudes, contradict themselves, resist the patterns of their upbringing, and surprise you. A framework illuminates; it does not determine.</p>
        <p>What we are claiming is this: understanding a culture's pillars gives you a better starting point for genuine curiosity than you had before. It opens a door. Walking through it is up to you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Vision -->
  <section class="about-section about-section--alt">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <div class="about-text-block">
        <h2 class="about-h2">What we hope for</h2>
        <p>We hope for a world where people reaching across cultural distance do so with genuine curiosity rather than inherited suspicion. Where the first instinct when encountering a stranger from a different background is not fear or judgment, but: <em>"Tell me how you see the world."</em></p>
        <p>We hope that Spirit Mirror gives people around the world a place to show their best — to be understood on their own terms, in their own depth, rather than through the reductive lens of headlines and stereotypes.</p>
        <p>Every culture in the world has something beautiful, complex, and worth understanding at depth. We are building the infrastructure for that understanding to be accessible to anyone with genuine curiosity and a willingness to listen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-aside">
        <div class="about-callout">
          <p>"To know another soul fully is to find reflected in them the whole range of human possibility."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The future -->
  <section class="about-section">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <div class="about-text-block">
        <h2 class="about-h2">This is just the beginning</h2>
        <p>We have started with six countries that we believe represent a wide range of cultural experiences. But every country in the world deserves this kind of depth and care. Every culture has something irreplaceable to offer.</p>
        <p>If you share our vision — if you believe that understanding is the foundation of connection — we want to hear from you. Help us build Spirit Mirror into something truly global. Every culture. Every pillar. Every human being on this planet, seen and understood.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>

</Layout>

<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,700;0,900;1,400&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600&family=DM+Sans:opsz,wght@9..40,300;9..40,400;9..40,600&display=swap');

  /* ── Tokens ─────────────────────────────── */
  :root {
    --bg: #f5f8f4;
    --bg-alt: #edf3ed;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --text-light: #4b4540;
    --muted: #6b6560;
    --accent: #2d7a4a;
    --accent-light: rgba(45,122,74,0.08);
    --border: #e0ddd5;
    --radius: 12px;
  }

  :global(.site-header) {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.95) !important;
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px) !important;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45,122,74,0.1) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05) !important;
  }
  :global(.site-logo) {
    color: var(--accent) !important;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif !important;
  }
  :global(.site-root) {
    background: var(--bg) !important;
  }

  /* ── Hero ─────────────────────────────── */
  .about-hero {
    padding: 120px 24px 80px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero-inner {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .about-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* ── Sections ─────────────────────────────── */
  .about-section {
    padding: 72px 24px;
    background: var(--white);
  }

  .about-section--alt {
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .about-section-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-text-block {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .about-h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .about-text-block p {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  .about-text-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-text-block p + p {
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* ── Quote / Callout ─────────────────────────────── */
  .about-aside {
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  .about-quote {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .about-callout {
    background: var(--accent-light);
    border: 1px solid rgba(45,122,74,0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 28px 32px;
  }

  .about-callout p {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Pillars ─────────────────────────────── */
  .about-pillars {
    margin: 40px 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .about-pillar {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 24px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .about-section--alt .about-pillar {
    background: var(--white);
  }

  .about-pillar:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .about-pillar-icon {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .about-pillar-content h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }

  .about-pillar-content p {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── CTA ─────────────────────────────── */
  .about-cta {
    padding: 80px 24px;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--white);
  }

  /* ── Footer override ─────────────────────────────── */
  :global(.about ~ footer),
  footer {
    background: var(--bg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 40px 24px;
  }

  :global(.about ~ footer .footer-inner),
  .footer-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  :global(.about ~ footer .footer-logo),
  .footer-logo {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  :global(.about ~ footer .footer-copy),
  .footer-copy {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Mobile ─────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-pillars {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-hero {
      padding: 100px 24px 60px;
    }

    .about-section {
      padding: 48px 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
